folder: Grand Central Parkwa & Horace Harding Boulevard, Queens, NY
text:
Grand Central Parkway, north from Horace Harding Boulevard and Corona Avenue, showing the new highway that was cut through the Corona ash dumps. This area was incorporated into Flushing Meadow Park. The temporary bridge over the parkway is at 54th Avenue.

November 10, 1936
Views 1,2

P. L. Sperr
title: Queens: Grand Central Parkwa - Horace Harding Boulevard

folder: Grand Central Parkwa & Horace Harding Boulevard, Queens, NY
text:
Grand Central Parkway, north from Horace Harding Boulevard, showing two stages in the construction of the new borough-wide highway. Views 1 and 2 still show parts of the Corona dumps through which the highway was cut. View 3 also shows early construction of buildings of the World's Fair (1939-40).

P. L. Sperr

Views 1,2: Nov. 10, 1936
View 3: Oct. 5, 1937
